                  <p>MDCCLXXXVI.</p>
                  <p>
                     <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178610250236"></xptr>THE WHOLE PROCEEDINGS UPON THE</p>
                  <p>KING's Commission of the Peace, Oyer and Terminer, and Gaol Delivery for the CITY of LONDON, &amp;c.</p>
                  <p>Continuation of the Trial of 
                  <persName id="t17861025-134-person1548">
                     Edward
                      Evans
                  <interp inst="t17861025-134-person1548" type="surname" value="Evans"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17861025-134-person1548" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17861025-134-person1548" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
               .</p>
               </div1>
               <p>Court. I think you said that before that Monday when you met him at Haslam's, you had not seen him for a dozen years? - I never saw him while I lived with my master, nor at the meeting with the taylor. (The piece shewn to Rogers.) It was one just like that, a heavy piece, I cannot be sure; it was a whole piece.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. They all run the same length; this piece is worth three pounds ten shillings, or four pounds.</p>
               <p>Court. Then this man made a very hard bargain if it was worth then four pounds.</p>
               <p>Court to Rogers. What did he give you for the piece of plain muslin? - To the best of my knowledge, four guineas and a half.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called two witnesses to his character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17861025-134-verdict710" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17861025-134-verdict710" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Court. Let this prisoner receive sentence with the others concerned in the same transaction.</p>
               <p>Tried by the London Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
            </div1>
